<br>
There really isn't a good reason to nerf our chants in PvP.  I posted a thread asking Sony to tell us if the nerf was intentional or a mistake and they never responded. That thread stayed on the first page for over a week, and Sony's Ryan was able to post here quickly regarding the upcoming  Improved Instrument and Singing Mastery AAs ( Nerf to PvP Chants + New Chaos Chant = Reason for nerf).<br>
<br>
I infer that Sony feels that the upcoming Chaos Chant would be overpowered if they didn't modify our other chants. I think they did it purposefully for this reason. Otherwise, they would have responded to my post.<br>
<br>
The real concern I have is that usually ancient songs are not available for almost all of the bards on a server. Nerfing our chants in PvP really has decreased my enjoyment of the game (even though I play on a blue server). In part I made my bard and built his skills on his ability to PvP, and eliminating his only real offensive ability just doesn't sit well with many of us.<br>
<br>
I hope Sony reads this and does NOT make the new ancient song essentially unattainable by all bards except those few in the top one or two guilds on a server. I hope they at least do something along the lines that they did in LDON--that is, with LDON Sony allowed bards who were not able to join the top guild or guilds on a server able to keep developing their character through the use of adventure points. It takes quite a bit of time, but in LDON you can get some very nice upgrades. <br>
<br>
I hope most bards will be given some mechanism to get this song apart from being a member of one of the top one or two guilds on a server.<br>
<br>
<br>
