on is that the cause was related to one thing only:  Bards were able to solo, and SONY feels that bards belong in a group.<br>
<br>
Sony has done everything it can to make bards a group-oriented class, improving their capability to pull with lull and FM, decreasing group downtime with CoM, increasing group DPS with Zek, DS songs, and the Riz line--the list goes on.  All of their hard work and the intrepid bard class does the unthinkable:  we figure out how to solo.<br>
<br>
The Devs at Sony have never been able to accept that some people play this game in short bursts (making it difficult to find a group / raid) or to just play alone.  Since the AE kiting nerf, I have simply focused on tradeskills and raiding.  I rarely xp anymore, and I usually won't bother putting a group together to be mind-numbingly bored in LDoN (YMMV, it's my personal choice/opinion).  <br>
<br>
Losing the capability to solo--both via AE kiting and Chant kiting has hurt many bards, myself included.  It has also taken a lot of my enjoyment out of the game:  at this point I simply play to raid.  My 340+ AAs will likely only go up slowly, my tradeskills have been mastered (Aid Grimel done!) and I've farmed just about every rare piece of bard gear that I'm interested in (Wand of Imperceptibility, Tiny Cloak of Darkest Night, for instance).  <br>
<br>
My hope at this point is that GoD will provide some content that will again pique my interests.  Otherwise I'll log on to raid, and then log off, mainly because Sony has taken away those things that I previously enjoyed, and logged on day after day to enjoy.<br>
